<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-271-537  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 271 537.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  Jan 16 1989 n400 p27(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Study: scrap export curbs. (National Research Council)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Peterson, Stacey.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The National Research Council's (NRC's) yearlong report, initiatedat the request of the US State Department, indicates that exportrules for widely available and uncontrollable computertechnologies should be done away with.andP;  The report, intended toapprise the incoming Bush administration of the situation in theinternational computer market, concludes that US efforts torestrict exports of computer technology to the Eastern Bloc arefailing.andP;  The NCR committee of industry and academic expertsrecommended that the government ease restrictions on such exports,at least to Western Europe and Japan, and should insteadconcentrate on controlling exports of critical defenseapplications.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ExportGovernment RegulationStudyComputer IndustryTechnology TransferNational Research Councilm International Trade.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>